			<div class="content" id="post-content-4583296">
									

<p>I've seen this develop from before Arcadia became an official group, going from an idea the author couldn't stop talking about to a draft he wouldn't stop working on until it was just right. The massive effort here is pretty spectacular, along with the multimedia showcase. While there are little bits here and there I would've written differently, the mystery and story at play here are strong and I enjoy reading it even after having seen it through every phase of its development. +1</p>
<p>e: For clarity, I wrote some or all of what's in the final containment procedures and newspaper section, along with probably some other smaller bits throughout, but I do not wish for any sort of co-author credit. Popsioak deserves it all for himself. I just helped around the edges.</p>

							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p><em>Whether you like it or not, history is on our side. We will bury you!</em></p>

