<p>Okay so I keep putting off explaining my vote here. I gave this a -1.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[+]&nbsp;Open&nbsp;for&nbsp;my&nbsp;actual&nbsp;thoughts</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Good things: this is a technical marvel, like I'm really impressed at the level of production that's gone into this, with the custom art, the video and the audio, and the general presentation is supremely pretty.</p>
<p>Unfortunately, the big issue for me is that it reads,,,super blandly? Like particularly the first addendum here which is just, more description, a note the reader has no context for at this point and a newspaper article about a person who again has not been tied into the anomaly here. This means it comes across as a big info-dump of material that doesn't have any meaning for me, or drive the narrative forward.</p>
<p>A lot of the following logs feel like they're lacking the required context for me to understand their significance and it ends up feeling a touch frustrating for me to read. It kinda feels like I'm reading a murder mystery story but from chapter 2, without all the context of the first chapter introducing the victim and the detective and all that. And I mean, I guess on some level this is 'expected' since it's deliberately framed as a mystery for the reader to solve but it feels&#8230;unappealing for me personally to want to read or solve.</p>
</div>
